Everyone has a north node and a south node in their chart, and they are found in two signs that are opposite to one another. When you get familiar with what the nodes mean for you, you can see what areas you will to move toward to feel more fulfilled in your life. Also, the signs in which your nodes fall indicate what signs the eclipses were happening in when you were born, so people born within about an 18 month period of each other will have their nodes in the same signs.
These are the two rising signs that are about to have the biggest career year. These transits don’t come around often either, once every 12 (Jupiter) and 18-19 years (North Node) so get excited!

Plus, if you have any of these planets in the signs they rule in your chart (i.e. having Mars in Scorpio or Venus in Taurus) it’s easier for you to tap into the qualities associated with that planet than it might be for other people.

Annual profections - an ancient astrological timing technique that shows what general themes come up at specific ages. On the first slide locate your age and what house that’s associated with (house are labeled in the innermost ring) then check the second slide to see the themes that fit with that particular house. You can expect those themes to come up strongly for that entire year of your life. The cycle repeats itself every 12 years once every house has been activated. You can go way more in depth on this technique, but I wanted to give a little intro to it.

Are you guilty of googling your astrological compatibility? This weeks episode is one for you —> 

In this captivating episode, Caggie talks to Alice Bell, the author of “Trust Your Timing” and an astrologer for British Vogue. Alice takes us on her journey into the mystical world of astrology, where she discovered it as a means to refine her sense of spirituality. She shares how practicing the art of reading people’s birth charts became a profound learning experience, allowing her to understand that there’s an intricate timing for everything, and life unfolds as it’s meant to.

Alice delves into the fascinating concept of transits and their role in our birth charts, emphasizing the importance of looking beyond the surface when it comes to compatibility. She enlightens us on the nuances of astrological connections in dating, stressing that the quest for a perfect chart match isn’t necessary. Alice discusses key elements like the ascendant and descendant lines, shedding light on the significance of Venus as it relates to personal aesthetics and surface-level attractions. Moreover, she provides invaluable insights into what to watch out for in potential relationships to avoid negative consequences, all while exploring Caggie’s intriguing birth chart reading and the pivotal role of nodes in discovering one’s life purpose. Join us for an enriching conversation that delves into the depths of astrology and the art of trusting divine timing.
